22 March 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC)
------------------------------------
- interface/CDMSGeometryManager:  NEW class to provide "singleton" versions
  of geometry components, so all cross-dependencies can be satisfied without
  having to pass pointers around.

- interface/CDMSGeomMessenger.cc:  Use GeometryManager to get detector
  components.

- interface/CDMSGeomConstructor.cc:  Do not delete detector components here;
  now owned by GeometryManager.

- 7tower-draw.mac:  Add central "tipped" view showing tower layout
- 7tower-shield.mac:  Adjust viewer configuration
- bare-shield.mac:  Reduce verbosity
- shield-draw.mac:  Set ZIP to 4" dimensions

15 February 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC) (cdms-ggeom-V00-03-13)
--------------------------------------------------------------
- CDMSMultiTowerConstruction.cc, CDMSShieldConstruction.cc,
  CDMSTowerConstruction.cc, CDMSTowerSupportConstruction.cc,
  CDMSVesselConstruction.cc, CDMSZipConstruction.cc: Report component total
  mass (G4LogicalVolume::GetMass()) at end of BuildGeometry(), just before
  logical volume is returned.

11 February 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC) (cdms-ggeom-V00-03-12)
--------------------------------------------------------------
- interface/CDMSGeomMessenger.cc:  Add "shield" as Detector option, to draw
  empty veto shielding for test purposes.

- detectors/CDMSShieldConstruction.cc:  Allow user to set zero veto panels,
  to get just poly/lead shells.  Fix bugs in calculation of shielding cylinders.

- bare-shield.mac, bare-veto.mac: Draw empty shielding, with and without
  scintillator veto panels.

10 February 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC)
---------------------------------------
- detectors/CDMSMultiTowerConstruction.cc:  Move tower update earlier in
  FillExtraParameters(), simplify one diagnostic message.

- detectors/CDMSTowerPattern:  Resolve bug caused by tower registration
  change below.  Separate tower parameters from UseTower() function, so they
  can be updated by GeneratePattern(), e.g., after an Optimize() call, and
  add a generic function so "any" parameter change can trigger reset().

5 February 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC)
--------------------------------------
- detectors/CDMSMultiTowerConstruction.cc:  Register Tower with TowerPattern
  in ctor.

- detectors/CDMSTowerPattern:  Add new Optimize(mass) function to work out
  "best guess" tower layout and number of ZIPs per tower, to achieve desired
  target mass.  Currently starts with user's parameters and tweaks them to
  get a convex pattern as close to target mass as possible.  Required some
  supporting code changes.

- detectors/CDMSTowerConstruction.hh:  Add accessor to return ZIP geometry.

- detectors/CDMSZipConstruction:  Add accessors to return G4Material pointers.

- interface/CDMSTowerPatternMessenger:  Add new command to call Optimize().

4 February 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC) (cdms-ggeom-V00-03-11)
-------------------------------------------------------------
- detectors/CDMSTowerPattern.cc:  Add missing "return" for triplet core.
- 7tower-draw.mac: Change output mode to "pixmap" for drawable result.
- shield-draw.mac: Change output mode to "pixmap," use 7-tower detector.
- zip+source.mac: Fix config parameters for Am-241 source plate.

26 January 2011  Dennis Wright (SLAC) (cdms-ggeom-V00-03-10)
------------------------------------------------------------
- add sensitivity to veto scintillator panels, and magenta squares to
  veto hit display
- add classes CDMSVetoHit and CDMSVetoSD
- to be used with tag cdms-actions-V00-01-02 or later

26 January 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC)
--------------------------------------
- detectors/CDMSTowerPattern:  Rewrite hexagonal layout algorithm: towers
  are built in ring order (not index order), and outermost partial ring has
  positions sorted by radius to ensure most compact filling.  Move SetCenter()
  implementation to .cc file, if pattern already generated, just shift
  positions to new center, rather than recomputing from scratch.

23 January 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC)
--------------------------------------
- detectors/CDMSTowerPattern:  Finish implementing "triplet" hexagonal
  layout.  Complete "rings" are positioned correctly, but partial rings have
  uniform "phi" spacing, rather than minimizing radial extent.

22 January 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC)
--------------------------------------
- interface/CDMS_UIcmdShieldLayer.cc:  Fix unitialized loop variable.

- detectors/CDMSTowerPattern:  Add alternative hexagonal layout, with
  three towers in a triangle around the center point.  Refactored layout
  calculations to support both models; "triplet" version is not yet fully
  implemented or selected.

21 January 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC) (cdms-ggeom-V00-03-09)
-------------------------------------------------------------
- detectors/CDMSTowerPattern:  Replace "magic number" layout codes with
  enumerator, and include generic "hexagonal" close packing, to support
  "Option B" design.

- interface/CDMSTowerPatternMessenger:  Make "Code" take a string input, and
  map strings onto new enumerator values (see above).

- *.mac:  Replace "/CDMS/Layout/Code <number>" with new strings (ring, grid)

21 January 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC)
--------------------------------------
- 7tower-shield.mac:  Complete 100kg strawman detector, with shielding.
  Generates 1000 surface-electron events at center of detector.

- 7tower-draw.mac:  Reduce verbosity of vis commands.

- *.mac:  Following discussion in GEANT4 Hypernews
(http://hypernews.slac.stanford.edu/HyperNews/geant4/get/visualization/602.html)
  replace all viewpointThetaPhi directives with "upVector" to set
  orientation of dectector.

- detectors/CDMSZipSD.cc:  Suppress diagnostic printout.

- detectors/CDMSMultiTowerGeometry:  Modify placement functions so that
  towers are always put inside vacuum vessel; latter may optionally be placed
  inside veto shielding.  Fixes an overlap problem seen with 7tower-shield.mac.

15 January 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC) (cdms-ggeom-V00-03-08)
-------------------------------------------------------------
- detectors/CDMSShieldConstruction:  Handle arbitrary regular polygons
  (even- or odd-sided) for side veto panels.  Each middle panel is checked
  geometrically for intersection with the two cryostat pipe stems, and
  appropriately penetrations are made, at whatever angle is necessary.  At
  corners, adjacent panels may have partial holes cut in the overlap region.
  A collection of support functions are added to perform the calculations:

    G4bool PanelIntersectsVacStem(G4int index, G4double& panelY);
    G4bool PanelIntersectsFridgeStem(G4int index, G4double& panelY);
    G4LogicalVolume* MakeVacHoleInPanel(G4VSolid* panel, G4int index,
                                      G4double holeY);
    G4LogicalVolume* MakeFridgeHoleInPanel(G4VSolid* panel, G4int index,
                                      G4double holeY);
    G4LogicalVolume* MakePipeHoleInPanel(G4VSolid* panel, G4int index,
                                       G4double radius, G4double holeY,
                                       G4double holeZ);
  
    void GetCornersOfPanel(G4int index, G4Point3D& right, G4Point3D& left);
    G4double DistanceToPipe(const G4Point3D& right, const G4Point3D& left);

- interface/CDMSShieldMessenger.cc:  Simplify range limit on side panels,
  to require only N>2.  With above changes, any regular polygon is supported.

14 January 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC)
--------------------------------------
- interface/CDMSShieldMessenger:  Add range limit for NSidePanels<=12, to
  avoid multiple penetrations at corners.  To support fully general case,
  would need to compare boundary of pipe stems with panel corners, and
  puncture more than one, and would need to apply rotated penetrations.

- detectors/CDMSShieldConstruction.cc:  Determine mother "radius" (X/Y half
  length) by applying middle-panel transforms directly to outermost corner.  

13 January 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC) (cdms-ggeom-V00-03-07)
-------------------------------------------------------------
- interface/CDMS_UIcmdShieldLayer.cc:  Set parameter names for panel counts.

- interface/CDMSShieldMessenger: Use CDMSMessengerBase base class.  Use
  CDMS_UIcmdShieldLayer in place of blocks of repeated parameters.  Add all
  "missing" commands for adjustable parameters, with range limits on panel
  counts (dimensions ought to be range limited as well).

- detectors/CDMSShieldConstruction: Drop individual layer parameter
  functions.  Widths and shifts of side panels computed using trig to allow
  for arbitrary polygons.  Refactor PlaceBarrelVeto() to do each side ring
  separately.  Compute mother-volume dimensions from veto panel positions.

- detectors/CDMSTowerSupportConstruction:  Increase verbosity level for some
  computational sanity checks.

- shield-draw.mac:  Turn off verbosity.

12 January 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC)
--------------------------------------
- interface/CDMS_UIcmdShieldLayer:  New G4UIcommand subclass to handle all
  four shielding layer parameters (plus unit) in one line.

- detectors/CDMSShieldConstruction.hh:  Add LayerData::Copy() function to
  transfer numeric values between objects (strings are not copied unless
  implicit operator=() is used).  Replace "shiftFactor" with
  sideCornerOverlap dimensioned value.

11 January 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC) (cdms-ggeom-V00-03-06)
-------------------------------------------------------------
- detectors/CDMSShieldConstruction: Add parameters for number of veto panels
  (X and Y at top, total around cylinder), and compute coordinates by index.
  Replace hardwired arrays with std::vector<>.  Adjust computations of veto
  panel coordinates to eliminate corner collisions.  Add functions to set all
  layer parameters at once.

- overlaps_shield.mac:  Activate cylinder_test.  NO overlap errors reported.

9 January 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC) (cdms-ggeom-V00-03-05)
------------------------------------------------------------
- detectors/CDMSShieldConstruction: Tweaks to eliminate volume overlaps
  between shielding layers and pipe stems.  Veto panels still have overlaps.

- shield-draw.mac:  Reduce verbosity of visualization macros.
- overlaps_shield.mac:  Add commented-out cylinder_test action.

7 January 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC)
-------------------------------------
- detectors/CDMSShieldConstruction: Split PlaceVeto() into "endcap" and
  "barrel" functions. Move local parameters for veto panels to data members
  and compute values in FillVetoParameters().  Report values of computed
  parameters in PrintParameters().  Tweak hole positions to fix overlaps.

- detectors/CDMSTowerPattern.cc:  Allow user to set numberOfTowers = 0,
  without causing seg fault.

- detectors/CDMSVesselPattern.cc:  Check for nTowers==0 before building
  supports (avoid unnecessary work).

- shield-dawn.mac:  New macro to draw empty cryostat with shield, using the
  DAWN rendering to try to identify overlaps.  Not entirely successful.

- sheild-draw.mac:  Set number of towers to zero to simplify geometry.

6 January 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC) (cdms-ggeom-V00-03-04)
------------------------------------------------------------
- detectors/CDMSShieldConstruction: Replace parallel blocks of parameters
  for each shielding layer with an internal struct (LayerData), including
  name, material, and vis-attributes.  Simplify BuildShieldLayer() to take
  LayerData as input.  Provide operator<< for LayerData.  Add
  PlaceShieldLayer(const LayerData&) to simplify PlaceShielding().  Use
  rectangular box for mother volume, to enclose endcap scintillators without
  wasted space.

- labs/NoLab.cc:  Increase size of dummy volume to fully enclose shielding.

- *-draw.mac:  Add filename specifications for all drawings.

6 January 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC) (cdms-ggeom-V00-03-03)
------------------------------------------------------------
- shield-draw.mac, cryostat.mac:  Remove geometry overlaps test.  Done in
  separate overlaps_*.mac jobs.

- overlaps_shield.mac:  Run geometry testing on full veto shield configuration.

- detectors/CDMSShieldConstruction: Move layer-by-layer parameters from
  BuildShield() to FillExtraParameters(), defining them as data members.
  Split FillExtraParameters() into separate functions for groups of
  parameters.  Add all parameters to PrintParameters() output.

5 January 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC)
-------------------------------------
- shield-draw.mac:  New macro to show 7-tower system with shielding added,
  in side-view only, and run overlaps test.

- cryostat.mac: Add geometry overlaps test.

- detectors/CDMSVesselConstruction:  Rename some variables to clarify
  meaning, add list of pipe lengths for each stage, replace "PipeBaseLen"
  with "PipeOutsideLen" referencing only portion outside cryostat.  Replace
  usage of "[outer]" indexing with STL-compliant .back().  Compute list of
  pipe Z values as actual coordinates, not top/bottom offsets.

- detectors/CDMSShieldConstruction.cc:  Follow CDMSVesselConstruction
  changes, and align pipe penetrations with cryostat positions.  Mother
  volume still has some misalignment.

- interface/CDMSVesselMessenger.cc:  Follow changes to CDMSVesselConstruction. 

5 January 2011  Michael Kelsey (SLAC) (cdms-ggeom-V00-03-02)
------------------------------------------------------------
- interface/CDMSGeomConstructor: Drop "shield" activities here, move to
  become component of MultiTower detector.

- interface/CDMSGeomMessenger: Drop "shield" activities here, move to become
